# Trivy CVE Suppressions
# Reviewed and accepted vulnerabilities with no upstream fix available.
# All Dockerfiles run apt-get upgrade -y, so patches are picked up automatically
# when Debian publishes them. Last reviewed: 2026-03-01

# --- HIGH severity ---

# glibc: Integer overflow in memalign (libc6, libc-bin)
# Requires attacker control of both size (near PTRDIFF_MAX) and alignment args
# to memalign — not reachable in Python/FastAPI workloads.
CVE-2026-0861

# --- MEDIUM severity ---

# util-linux: Heap buffer overread in setpwnam() (bsdutils, login, mount,
# libblkid1, liblastlog2-2, libmount1, libsmartcols1, libuuid1, util-linux)
# Requires processing 256-byte usernames — not applicable to containerized
# Python services with fixed non-root user.
CVE-2025-14104

# curl: Pinned public key verification bypass (curl, libcurl4t64)
# Only affects CURLOPT_PINNEDPUBLICKEY usage — not used by Python httpx/urllib.
CVE-2025-13034

# glibc: wordexp returns uninitialized memory with WRDE_REUSE/WRDE_APPEND
# (libc-bin, libc6) — wordexp not called by Python runtime or dependencies.
CVE-2025-15281

# glibc: Information disclosure via zero-valued network query (libc-bin, libc6)
CVE-2026-0915

# sqlite: Integer overflow in FTS5 (libsqlite3-0)
# Application uses PostgreSQL, not SQLite for data storage.
CVE-2025-7709

# libtasn1: DoS via stack buffer overflow in asn1_expend_octet_string
# (libtasn1-6) — ASN.1 parsing not directly exposed to untrusted input.
CVE-2025-13151

# zlib: DoS via infinite loop in CRC32 combine functions (zlib1g)
CVE-2026-27171
